# Frontend environment. Copy to frontend/.env and adjust as needed.

# API origin. Leave UNSET for local dev — the Vite dev server proxies /api to
# the backend (same-origin), which is the intended dev setup. Only set this for
# a split-origin deployment, and point it at an https origin — a cross-origin
# http://localhost:PORT can be force-upgraded to https by a stale HSTS entry and
# fail to connect. Unset → falls back to window.location.origin (single-server).
# VITE_API_URL=

# --- Cloud upload ("Move to cloud") ---------------------------------------
# Optional. The frontend reads each provider's client id + redirect URI from the
# backend's /api/cloud/providers by default, so these are only needed to
# OVERRIDE those values. All are public (non-secret).
# Dropbox — see docs/dropbox-setup.md.
# VITE_DROPBOX_APP_KEY=
# VITE_DROPBOX_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/oauth/callback
# Google Drive — see docs/google-drive-setup.md.
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# VITE_GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/oauth/callback
